Post to #trading-scheduled-updates:

```
[CLOUD-TRADE-REC] {YYYY-MM-DD} | {HH:MM} UTC+8

Regime: {label}
Overlay Gates: SPY {ON/OFF} | QQQ {ON/OFF} | GSCI {ON/OFF} | BTC {ON/OFF}

PROMOTED ({n}): {asset} {Long/Short} Sum={x} | ... (or "None")
NEAR-MISS ({n}): {asset} Sum={x} missing {leg} | ... (or "None")

Checklist: {ALL PASS / BLOCKED — {reason}}
Heat: {x}% of 8% cap
Grade A gaps: {list or "None"}

File: trade-rec-{today}.md ✓ (GDrive) | {T.system/Trade/{today}/trade-rec-{today}.md}
```

---

## Note

This task fires at 19:00 UTC+8 — 2 hours before the local pipeline brief (20:08) and trade-rec (20:20). The `/daily-trade-rec` skill's delta-check gate (Step 0) will detect whether the 7pm upstream files differ from any prior run and proceed accordingly. The local 20:20 task will run again with the updated brief and news, producing the authoritative final rec. This cloud version is labeled Grade B supplementary context unless it is the only rec produced that day.

- Exit: Status (HIT_STOP/HIT_TARGET/EXPIRED/DISCRETIONARY_CLOSE), Exit_Price, Exit_Date, Days_to_Exit, Hypo_PnL_Pct.
- Stop move: don't edit ATR_Stop, append to Notes.

**Layer 3 — framework/memory-lessons.md:** Append one factual line. Non-routine adjustments only.

**Layer 4 — auto-memory (conditional):** Only for repeated/novel patterns.

**Layer 5 — Slack POSITION STATE SNAPSHOT (every event):**
After Layers 1–4 complete, post an updated snapshot to `#trading-scheduled-updates` so the cloud scheduled agent has current position context on its next fire. Single message, not a thread.

1. Resolve channel: `slack_search_channels(query="trading-scheduled-updates")` → pick exact-name match. Not found → log missing in rec, skip layer (do not fail the whole update).

2. Compose message. Lead tag `[POSITION-STATE]`. Use **plain text only** — no markdown tables (pipe-separator rows cause `invalid_blocks`). Format each position as a single pipe-delimited line:

```
[POSITION-STATE] {YYYY-MM-DD HH:MM UTC+8}

Open positions ({N}):
{Sig} | {Asset} | {Side} | Entry {price} | Stop {price} | Target {price or —} | Heat {X.X%} | {Thesis one-liner} | Invalidation: {condition}
(repeat one line per position)

Portfolio heat: {X.X%} | Sector exposure: {tech X%, crypto Y%, ...}
Circuit breaker: {none | reduced | defensive}
Watchlist promotions since last snapshot: {tickers or "none"}
Last closed trade: {asset, exit type, hypo_pnl or "none this week"}
